{
  "doc_id": "22928",
  "text": "The lower number of rats that developed tumors in the OTM group might also be explained by the reduction of the generation of ROS, assessed indirectly by the lower rate of lipid peroxidation. Metformin, owing to its antioxidant activity and to its effect decreasing the levels of circulating triglycerides, may contribute to the lower generation of ROS [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . In fact, previous data from our laboratory have shown the lowering effect of metformin on the generation of ROS in mesenteric arteries of obese-MSG rats without tumor [CITATION_5] .",
